Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:Disciples of Thrym are proficient with all simple and martial weapons, with all types of armor, and with shields.	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=WeaponProfMartial|TYPE=ArmorProfHeavy|TYPE=ShieldProf
Spells per Day			KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Spells per Day							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:A disciple of Thrym can cast a small number of divine spells. To cast a spell, the disciple must have a Wisdom score of at least 10 + the spell’s level. The disciple of Thrym’s spells are based on Wisdom, and saving throws against these spells have a DC of 10 + spell level + the disciple’s Wisdom modifier. A disciple of Thrym otherwise casts spells as a cleric does, although he cannot swap out prepared spells to spontaneously cast cure or inflict spells. The disciple’s spell list appears at the end of this prestige class description; when he prepares spells, he may select from any of the spells on this list.
Detect Fire				KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Detect Fire								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:At 1st level, the disciple of Thrym can detect fire at will as a cleric of a level equal to his class level.
Protection of Winter		KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Protection of Winter						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:At 1st level, the disciple of Thrym gains greater protection based on the local temperature. In cold areas (temperature at or below 40° F), he gains +1 sacred bonus on all saving throws and a +1 bonus to Armor Class. In areas of extreme cold (below –20° F), the sacred bonus is increased to +2 on all saves and AC.
Resistance to Fire		KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Resistance to Fire						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:At 2nd level, the disciple of Thrym gains resistance to fire 5. At 6th level, this increases to resistance to fire 10.
Powerful Grip			KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Powerful Grip							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:At 3rd level, the disciple of Thrym gains a damage bonus equal to half his Strength bonus when he attacks with a greataxe. This means he adds 2 times his Strength bonus on his damage rolls instead of 1–1/2 times his Strength bonus when wielding the weapon in two hands.
Frost Greataxe			KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Frost Greataxe							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:At 4th level, as a move action, the disciple of Thrym can cause a greataxe he wields to become sheathed in a layer of intense cold, granting the axe the frost special ability (+1d6 points of cold damage on a successful strike). If he lets go of the axe, the frost dissipates immediately; other wise it lasts for a number of rounds equal to his class level.
Agonizing Strike			KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Agonizing Strike							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:At 5th level, the disciple of Thrym gains the ability to focus all the anger and hatred in his frozen heart into a single blow once per day. He makes a normal melee attack; if he hits, he deals +1d6 points of cold damage for every two class levels (+2d6 at 5th, +3d6 at 6th, +4d6 at 8th, and +5d6 at 10th level). If the attack misses, the agonizing strike is still used up for the day. At 9th level, the disciple can perform this strike twice per day.
Dispel Fire				KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Dispel Fire								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:At 7th level, the disciple of Thrym can dispel fire as a cleric of the same level a number of times per day equal to 1 + his Charisma modifier.
Icy Greataxe			KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Icy Greataxe							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.57	DESC:At 8th level, as a move action, the disciple of Thrym can cause a greataxe he wields to become sheathed in a layer of intense cold, granting the axe the icy burst special ability (+1d6 points of cold damage on a successful strike, plus an extra 2d10 points of cold damage on a successful critical). If he lets go of the axe, the frost dissipates immediately, otherwise it lasts for a number of rounds equal to his class level.
Immunity to Fire			KEY:Disciple of Thrym ~ Immunity to Fire							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Disciple of Thrym Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:At 10th level, the disciple of Thrym gains immunity to fire, becoming prepared for the burning flames of Surtur that will destroy the multiverse.

# Frostrager
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Frostrager ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Frostrager Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.61	DESC:Frostragers gain no proficiency with any weapon, armor, or shields.
Frostrage				KEY:Frostrager ~ Frostrage								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Frostrager Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.61	DESC:While raging, the character grows larger and more massive, and his freezing sweat forms icicles as it streams out of his pores, coating his body in a glittering crust of ice. The frostrager’s actual size category does not change (nor does his space/reach), but he does gain a +4 natural armor bonus to Armor Class from the sheets of ice that form over his body. In addition, a frostrager’s unarmed attacks deal 1d6 points of damage plus 1d4 points of cold damage on a successful hit. If the frostrager is Small, his unarmed attack deals 1d4 points of damage, and if the frostrager is Large, his unarmed attack deals 1d8 points of damage.
Freezing Blood			KEY:Frostrager ~ Freezing Blood							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Frostrager Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.61	DESC:At 1st level, a frostrager’s blood becomes freezing cold. His wounds instantly freeze over and stop bleeding; he is immune to attacks that cause wounding effects. If reduced to negative hit points, he automatically stabilizes. He still takes 1 point of damage if he takes any actions while at 0 or negative hit points, however.
One-Two Punch			KEY:Frostrager ~ One-Two Punch							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Frostrager Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.61	DESC:At 2nd level, while making an unarmed attack, the frostrager may make one extra attack in a round at his highest base attack bonus, but each attack made in that round (the extra one and the normal ones) take a –2 penalty.
Absorb Cold				KEY:Frostrager ~ Absorb Cold								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Frostrager Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.61	DESC:At 3rd level, while raging, the frostrager not only gains immunity to cold, but it heals him. For every 2 points of cold damage that would have otherwise have been dealt by an attack, the frostrager heals 1 point of damage.
Improved Frostrage		KEY:Frostrager ~ Improved Frostrage							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Frostrager Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.61	DESC:At 4th level while raging, the frostrager’s natural armor bonus increases to +6. His unarmed attacks deal 1d8 points of damage plus 1d6 points of cold damage on a successful hit. If the frostrager is Small, his unarmed attack deals 1d6 points of damage, and if the frostrager is Large, his unarmed attack deals 2d6 points of damage.
Rend					KEY:Frostrager ~ Rend									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Frostrager Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.61	DESC:At 5th level, a frostrager gains the ability to rend a target. In any round that the frostrager hits the same foe with two or more unarmed attacks, he immediately deals an additional 2d8 points of damage (plus 1-1/2 times his Strength bonus), plus an additional 1d6 points of cold damage. If he is Small, his rend deals 2d6 points of damage; if he is Large, his rend deals 3d8 points of damage.

